# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — Files Git Should NOT Track
# =============================================================================
#
# WHAT IS .gitignore?
#   When you run "git add .", Git adds ALL changed files to the staging area.
#   But some files should NEVER go into your repo:
#     - Secrets (API keys, passwords)
#     - Local configuration (your editor settings)
#     - Large binary files (model weights, datasets)
#     - Generated files that can be recreated (Python bytecode, virtual envs)
#   .gitignore tells Git to skip these completely.
#
# WHY NOT COMMIT THE DATASET?
#   The Telco dataset is ~2MB. While small, best practice is to NOT commit
#   datasets to Git. Instead, document WHERE to get it (README). Datasets
#   can grow to GBs and Git is not designed for large binary files.
#
# WHY NOT COMMIT THE MODEL FILE?
#   model/best_model.pkl is a binary file that changes every training run.
#   Git can't meaningfully diff binary files, so each version bloats your
#   repo history. We'll handle model versioning with DVC in Project 3.
# =============================================================================

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python

# --- Virtual Environments ---
# Never commit your venv — it's huge and OS-specific
venv/
env/
.venv/
.env/

# --- Environment Variables / Secrets ---
# CRITICAL: never commit .env files — they often contain API keys
.env
.env.*
*.env

# --- Jupyter Notebooks ---
# Checkpoint files are auto-generated and don't need version control
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Data ---
# Datasets should not be committed — document where to download them
data/raw/*.csv
data/raw/*.zip
data/processed/*.csv

# --- ML Artifacts ---
# Committing model files so Render can load them at deploy time.
# In Project 3 we'll replace this with DVC for proper model versioning.
model/*.joblib
model/*.pt
model/*.h5

# --- IDE / Editor ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# --- OS Files ---
.DS_Store        # macOS
Thumbs.db        # Windows
desktop.ini

# --- MLflow ---
# mlruns/ is the local experiment database. It grows large and changes
# every training run — not useful to version in Git.
# In a team setting, you'd point MLflow at a shared server instead.
mlruns/
mlflow.db

# --- Testing ---
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
*.coverage

# --- Distribution / Build ---
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
